name: Chespin
flavorText: The quills on its head are usually soft.When it flexes them, the points becomeso hard and sharp that they can pierce rock.

name: Quilladin
flavorText: It relies on its sturdy shell to deflect predators’attacks. It counterattacks with its sharp quills.

name: Chesnaught
flavorText: Its Tackle is forceful enough to flip a 50-ton tank.It shields its allies from danger with its own body.

name: Fennekin
flavorText: Eating a twig fills it with energy,and its roomy ears give vent to airhotter than 390 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Braixen
flavorText: It has a twig stuck in its tail. Withfriction from its tail fur, it sets thetwig on fire and launches into battle.

name: Delphox
flavorText: It gazes into the flame at the tip ofits branch to achieve a focused state,which allows it to see into the future.

name: Froakie
flavorText: It secretes flexible bubbles from its chest and back.The bubbles reduce the damage it would otherwisetake when attacked.

name: Frogadier
flavorText: It can throw bubble-covered pebbles with precisecontrol, hitting empty cans up to a hundred feet away.

name: Greninja
flavorText: It creates throwing stars out of compressed water.When it spins them and throws them at high speed,these stars can split metal in two.

name: Bunnelby
flavorText: They use their large ears to dig burrows.They will dig the whole night through.

name: Diggersby
flavorText: With their powerful ears, they can heftboulders of a ton or more with ease.They can be a big help at construction sites.

name: Fletchling
flavorText: These friendly Pokémon send signalsto one another with beautiful chirpsand tail-feather movements.

name: Fletchinder
flavorText: From its beak, it expels embers that setthe tall grass on fire. Then it pounces onthe bewildered prey that pop out of the grass.

name: Talonflame
flavorText: In the fever of an exciting battle, itshowers embers from the gaps betweenits feathers and takes to the air.

name: Scatterbug
flavorText: When under attack from bird Pokémon,it spews a poisonous black powderthat causes paralysis on contact.

name: Spewpa
flavorText: It lives hidden within thicket shadows.When predators attack, it quickly bristles the furcovering its body in an effort to threaten them.

name: Vivillon
flavorText: Vivillon with many different patterns arefound all over the world. These patternsare affected by the climate of their habitat.

name: Litleo
flavorText: The stronger the opponent it faces,the more heat surges from its maneand the more power flows through its body.

name: Pyroar
flavorText: The male with the largest mane of fireis the leader of the pride.

name: Flabebe
flavorText: It draws out and controls the hidden powerof flowers. The flower Flabébé holdsis most likely part of its body.

name: Floette
flavorText: It flutters around fields of flowers and cares forflowers that are starting to wilt. It drawsout the hidden power of flowers to battle.

name: Florges
flavorText: It claims exquisite flower gardens as its territory,and it obtains power from basking in the energyemitted by flowering plants.

name: Skiddo
flavorText: Thought to be one of the first Pokémon to live inharmony with humans, it has a placid disposition.

name: Gogoat
flavorText: It can tell how its Trainer is feeling bysubtle shifts in the grip on its horns.This empathic sense lets them run as if one being.

name: Pancham
flavorText: It does its best to be taken seriously by its enemies,but its glare is not sufficiently intimidating.Chewing on a leaf is its trademark.

name: Pangoro
flavorText: Although it possesses a violent temperament,it won’t put up with bullying. It uses the leaf inits mouth to sense the movements of its enemies.

name: Furfrou
flavorText: Trimming its fluffy fur not only makesit more elegant but also increases theswiftness of its movements.

name: Espurr
flavorText: The organ that emits its intense psychic power issheltered by its ears to keep power from leaking out.

name: Meowstic-male
flavorText: When in danger, it raises its ears andreleases enough psychic power togrind a 10-ton truck into dust.

name: Honedge
flavorText: Apparently this Pokémon is born when adeparted spirit inhabits a sword. It attaches itselfto people and drinks their life force.

name: Doublade
flavorText: When Honedge evolves, it divides into two swords,which cooperate via telepathy to coordinate attacksand slash their enemies to ribbons.

name: Aegislash-shield
flavorText: Generations of kings were attended by thesePokémon, which used their spectral power tomanipulate and control people and Pokémon.

name: Spritzee
flavorText: It emits a scent that enraptures thosewho smell it. This fragrance changesdepending on what it has eaten.

name: Aromatisse
flavorText: It devises various scents, pleasant and unpleasant,and emits scents that its enemies dislike in orderto gain an edge in battle.

name: Swirlix
flavorText: To entangle its opponents in battle, it extrudeswhite threads as sweet and sticky as cotton candy.

name: Slurpuff
flavorText: It can distinguish the faintest of scents.It puts its sensitive sense of smell to useby helping pastry chefs in their work.

name: Inkay
flavorText: Opponents who stare at the flashing of thelight-emitting spots on its body becomedazed and lose their will to fight.

name: Malamar
flavorText: It wields the most compelling hypnotic powersof any Pokémon, and it forces others to dowhatever it wants.

name: Binacle
flavorText: Two Binacle live together on one rock.When they fight, one of them will moveto a different rock.

name: Barbaracle
flavorText: When they evolve, two Binacle multiply into seven.They fight with the power of seven Binacle.

name: Skrelp
flavorText: Camouflaged as rotten kelp, they sprayliquid poison on prey that approachesunawares and then finish it off.

name: Dragalge
flavorText: Their poison is strong enough to eat throughthe hull of a tanker, and they spit it indiscriminatelyat anything that enters their territory.

name: Clauncher
flavorText: They knock down flying prey by firingcompressed water from their massiveclaws like shooting a pistol.

name: Clawitzer
flavorText: Their enormous claws launch cannonballs ofwater powerful enough to pierce tanker hulls.

name: Helioptile
flavorText: They make their home in deserts. They cangenerate their energy from basking in the sun,so eating food is not a requirement.

name: Heliolisk
flavorText: They flare their frills and generate energy.A single Heliolisk can generate sufficientelectricity to power a skyscraper.

name: Tyrunt
flavorText: This Pokémon was restored from a fossil.If something happens that it doesn’t like,it throws a tantrum and runs wild.

name: Tyrantrum
flavorText: Thanks to its gargantuan jaws, which could shredthick metal plates as if they were paper, it wasinvincible in the ancient world it once inhabited.

name: Amaura
flavorText: This ancient Pokémon was restoredfrom part of its body that had beenfrozen in ice for over 100 million years.

name: Aurorus
flavorText: The diamond-shaped crystals on its bodyexpel air as cold as -240 degrees Fahrenheit,surrounding its enemies and encasing them in ice.

name: Sylveon
flavorText: It sends a soothing aura from itsribbonlike feelers to calm fights.

name: Hawlucha
flavorText: Although its body is small, its proficientfighting skills enable it to keep up withbig bruisers like Machamp and Hariyama.

name: Dedenne
flavorText: Its whiskers serve as antennas. By sending andreceiving electrical waves, it can communicatewith others over vast distances.

name: Carbink
flavorText: Born from the temperatures and pressuresdeep underground, it fires beams from thestone in its head.

name: Goomy
flavorText: The weakest Dragon-type Pokémon,it lives in damp, shady places, so itsbody doesn’t dry out.

name: Sliggoo
flavorText: It drives away opponents by excreting asticky liquid that can dissolve anything.Its eyes devolved, so it can’t see anything.

name: Goodra
flavorText: This very friendly Dragon-type Pokémonwill hug its beloved Trainer, leavingthat Trainer covered in sticky slime.

name: Klefki
flavorText: These key collectors threaten any attackersby fiercely jingling their keys at them.

name: Phantump
flavorText: These Pokémon are created whenspirits possess rotten tree stumps.They prefer to live in abandoned forests.

name: Trevenant
flavorText: It can control trees at will. It will trap peoplewho harm the forest, so they can never leave.

name: Pumpkaboo-average
flavorText: The pumpkin body is inhabited by a spirittrapped in this world. As the sun sets,it becomes restless and active.

name: Gourgeist-average
flavorText: Singing in eerie voices, they wandertown streets on the night of the new moon.Anyone who hears their song is cursed.

name: Bergmite
flavorText: It blocks opponents’ attacks with theice that shields its body. It uses cold airto repair any cracks with new ice.

name: Avalugg
flavorText: Its ice-covered body is as hard as steel.Its cumbersome frame crushes anything thatstands in its way.

name: Noibat
flavorText: They live in pitch-black caves. Their enormous earscan emit ultrasonic waves of 200,000 hertz.

name: Noivern
flavorText: They fly around on moonless nightsand attack careless prey. Nothing canbeat them in a battle in the dark.

name: Xerneas
flavorText: Legends say it can share eternal life.It slept for a thousand years in the formof a tree before its revival.

name: Yveltal
flavorText: When this legendary Pokémon’s wings andtail feathers spread wide and glow red,it absorbs the life force of living creatures.

name: Zygarde-50
flavorText: When the Kalos region’s ecosystem falls intodisarray, it appears and reveals its secret power.

name: Diancie
flavorText: A sudden transformation of Carbink,its pink, glimmering body is said to bethe loveliest sight in the whole world.

name: Hoopa
flavorText: This troublemaker sends anythingand everything to faraway placesusing its loop, which can warp space.

name: Volcanion
flavorText: It lets out billows of steam and disappears intothe dense fog. It’s said to live in mountainswhere humans do not tread.
